spirit:field.spirit:name: RKEY
spirit:field.spirit:description: Reset Key - Firmware must write a value of 0xA to this field to cause a soft reset of the Interrupt registers of AXI IIC controller. Writing any other value results in an AXI transaction acknowledgement with SLVERR and no reset occurs.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit must be set before any other CR bits have any effect 0 - resets and disables the AXI IIC controller but not the registers or FIFOs 1 - enables the AXI IIC controller

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_FIFO Reset
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit must be set to flush the FIFO if either (a) arbitration is lost or (b) if a transmit error occurs 0 - transmit FIFO normal operation 1 - resets the transmit FIFO

spirit:field.spirit:name: MSMS
spirit:field.spirit:description: When this bit is changed from 0 to 1, the AXI IIC bus interface generates a START condition in master mode. When this bit is cleared, a STOP condition is generated and the AXI IIC bus interface switches to slave mode. When this bit is cleared by the hardware, because arbitration for the bus has been lost, a STOP condition is not generated

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit selects the direction of master/slave transfers. 0 - selects an AXI IIC receive 1 - selects an AXI IIC transmit

spirit:field.spirit:name: TXAK
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit specifies the value driven onto the sda line during acknowledge cycles for both master and slave recievers. 0 - acknowledge 1 - not-acknowledge

spirit:field.spirit:name: RSTA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Writing a 1 to this bit generates a repeated START condition on the bus if the AXI IIC bus interface is the current bus master. Attempting a repeated START at the wrong time, if the bus is owned by another master, results in a loss of arbitration. This bit is reset when the repeated start occurs. This bit must be set prior to writing the new address to the TX_FIFO or DTR

spirit:field.spirit:name: GC_EN
spirit:field.spirit:description: Setting this bit High allows the AXI IIC to respond to a general call address. 0 - General Call Disabled 1 - General Call Enabled

spirit:field.spirit:name: ABGC
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit is set to 1 when another master has issued a general call and the general call enable bit is set to 1, CR(6) = 1.

spirit:field.spirit:name: AAS
spirit:field.spirit:description: When the address on the IIC bus matches the slave address in the Address register (ADR), the IIC bus interface is being addressed as a slave and switches to slave mode. If 10-bit addressing is selected this device only responds to a 10-bit address or general call if enabled. This bit is cleared when a stop condition is detected or a repeated start occurs. 0 - indicates not being addressed as a slave 1 - indicates being addressed as a slave

spirit:field.spirit:name: BB
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit indicates the status of the IIC bus. This bit is set when a START condition is detected and cleared when a STOP condition is detected. 0 - indicates the bus is idle 1 - indicates the bus is busy

spirit:field.spirit:name: ARW
spirit:field.spirit:description: When the IIC bus interface has been addressed as a slave (AAS is set), this bit indicates the value of the read/write bit sent by the master. This bit is only valid when a complete transfer has occurred and no other transfers have been initiated. 0 - indicates master writing to slave 1 - indicates master reading from slave

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_FIFO_Full
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit is set High when the transmit FIFO is full.

spirit:field.spirit:name: RX_FIFO_Full
spirit:field.spirit:description: This bit is set High when the receive FIFO is full. This bit is set only when all 16 locations in the FIFO are full, regardless of the compare value field of the RX_FIFO_PIRQ register.

spirit:field.spirit:name: RX_FIFO_Empty
spirit:field.spirit:description: This is set High when the receive FIFO is empty.

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_FIFO_Empty
spirit:field.spirit:description: This is set High when the transmit FIFO is empty.

spirit:field.spirit:name: D7_D0
spirit:field.spirit:description: If the dynamic stop bit is used and the AXI IIC is a master receiver, the value is the number of bytes to receive.

spirit:field.spirit:name: Start
spirit:field.spirit:description: The dynamic start bit can be used to send a start or repeated start sequence on the IIC bus. A start sequence is generated if the MSMS = 0, a repeated start sequence is generated if the MSMS = 1.

spirit:field.spirit:name: Stop
spirit:field.spirit:description: The dynamic stop bit can be used to send an IIC stop sequence on the IIC bus after the last byte has been transmitted or received.

spirit:field.spirit:name: D7_D0
spirit:field.spirit:description: IIC Receive Data

spirit:field.spirit:name: Slave_Address
spirit:field.spirit:description: Address used by the IIC bus interface when in slave mode.

spirit:field.spirit:name: Occupancy_Value
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit[3] is the MSB. A binary value of 1001 indicates that 10 locations are full in the FIFO

spirit:field.spirit:name: Occupancy_Value
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit[3] is the MSB. A binary value of 1001 indicates that 10 locations are full in the FIFO

spirit:field.spirit:name: MSB of Slave Address
spirit:field.spirit:description: Three MSBs of the 10-bit address used by the AXI IIC bus interface when in slave mode.

spirit:register.spirit:name: RX_FIFO_PIRQ
spirit:register.spirit:description: Recieve FIFO Programmable Depth Interrupt Register

spirit:field.spirit:name: Compare Value
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit[3] is the MSB. A binary value of 1001 implies that when 10 locations in the receive FIFO are filled, the receive FIFO interrupt is set.

spirit:field.spirit:name: General Purpose Outputs
spirit:field.spirit:description: The LSB (Bit[0]) is the first bit populated

spirit:field.spirit:name: TSUSTA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Setup time for a repeated START condition.

spirit:field.spirit:name: TSUSTO
spirit:field.spirit:description: Setup time for a repeated STOP condition.

spirit:field.spirit:name: THDSTA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Hold time for a repeated START condition.

spirit:field.spirit:name: TSUDAT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Data Setup time

spirit:field.spirit:name: TBUF
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bus free time between a STOP and START condition

spirit:field.spirit:name: THIGH
spirit:field.spirit:description: High Period of the scl clock.

spirit:field.spirit:name: TLOW
spirit:field.spirit:description: Low Period of scl clock.

spirit:field.spirit:name: THDDAT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Data Hold time

spirit:modelParameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI_ACLK_FREQ_HZ
spirit:modelParameter.spirit:displayName: C S Axi Aclk Freq Hz

spirit:modelParameter.spirit:name: C_SCL_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:modelParameter.spirit:displayName: SCL Inertial delay filter value (in AXI clocks)

spirit:modelParameter.spirit:name: C_SDA_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:modelParameter.spirit:displayName: SDA Inertial delay value (in AXI clocks)

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SDA_LEVEL
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter is used during transmit throttling when the AXI IIC acts as master transmitter.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TEN_BIT_ADR
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter enables or disables the 10-bit addressing mode. Logic resource savings result when 10-bit addressing is disabled

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: AXI_ACLK_FREQ_MHZ
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specifies (but does not set) the frequency of the AXI4-Lite interface.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_GPO_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter sets the width of the general purpose output vector. If the user does not connect anything to this port, then logic optimization removes any resources associated with it.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SCL_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specifies the number of S_AXI_ACLK cycles used to define the width of the pulse rejection on SCL signals

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SDA_INERTIAL_DELAY
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter specify the number of S_AXI_ACLK cycles used to define the width of the pulse rejection on SDA signals

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: IIC_FREQ_KHZ
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter determines the approximate frequency of the master mode generated SCL clock signal (Hz)
